        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 20 at 11:00PM CST by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1100 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marion, or over Cibolo, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Braunfels, Schertz, Seguin, Cibolo, McQueeney, Marion, Santa
Clara, New Berlin, Geronimo, Zuehl, Nolte, and Zipp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
